[src:1973-oil-crisis/17-july-revolution] In the ensuing years, Wolfe-Hunnicutt states that Saddam "succeeded in consolidating a formidable political regime ... where so many others had failed," including co-opting Yahya's intention to nationalize the IPC with the help of the Soviet Union.
[src:1973-oil-crisis/17-july-revolution] Wolfe-Hunnicutt states there was "a significant American role in the events that brought the Ba'th to power" in 1968.
